  "text": "These and other (hitherto experimental) ICD inducers have been viewed as conventional forms of anticancer therapy, exerting antineoplastic effects via cytostatic or cytotoxic mechanisms. However, accumulating evidence indicates that the full-blown therapeutic potential of these molecules relies on the host immune system [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . Thus, we propose to classify ICD inducers as a form of active anticancer immunotherapy.",
